@startuml adr-supabase-native-rev3
title Supabase-native (Rev 3): GoTrue -> app_user_id -> app.current_uid() -> app.can_read_doc, and Slice-1 Emission

' ===========================================================================
' PART A: identity flow grounded on the LIVE shipped platform (resolves C1, C9)
'   Live objects: 20260623130000_app_schema_and_identity.sql (hook + app.current_uid)
'                 20260624141500_engine_auth_scope_helpers.sql (can_read_doc, etc.)
'                 api/_lib/supabase-session.js (provision + mintTokenHash chokepoint)
' ===========================================================================

package "Sign-in & Identity (GoTrue) -- ALL LIVE ON PROD" {
  class GoogleSignIn {
    + email
  }
  class "supabase-session.js (shared chokepoint)" as SessionMint {
    + provisionSupabaseUser(email)  (idempotent)
    + mintSupabaseTokenHash(email)  -> verifyOtp(token_hash)
    + NO signInWithIdToken path (Rev-2 was wrong)
  }
  class GoTrue {
    + issues session JWT
    + runs custom_access_token_hook on every mint
  }
  class "custom_access_token_hook (LIVE)" as Hook {
    + match lower(email) -> public.users
    + inject claims = { app_user_id = public.users.id (u178), app_role }  FROZEN
    + NO branch claim (state read live, K7)
  }
  class "public.users (canonical actor)" as Users {
    + id : text (u178)  <-- app_user_id keyspace
    + email, role, branch
    + service_states : jsonb  (["VIC","ACT"])
    + active, auth_user_id
  }
}

GoogleSignIn --> SessionMint : verify + provision
SessionMint --> GoTrue : token_hash -> session
GoTrue --> Hook : on token mint
Hook --> Users : lower(email) lookup -> id (u178)

' ---- LIVE shared scope helpers the engine CONSUMES (does not re-author) ----
package "LIVE shared app.* helpers (20260624141500)" {
  class "app.current_uid()" as CurUid {
    + reads request.jwt.claims->>'app_user_id'
    + works in PostgREST AND Realtime
  }
  class "app.is_admin()" as IsAdmin {
    + role='admin' OR branch='All' (read live)
  }
  class "app.state_in_scope(state) / user_state_ceiling()" as StateScope {
    + service_states ceiling, fail-closed on NULL state
  }
  class "app.can_read_doc(owner, state)  *" as CanReadDoc {
    + identity AND (is_admin OR owner=uid OR state_in_scope)
    + state NULL -> owner-or-admin (NOT fail-open)
  }
  class "app.users_v (security_invoker view)" as UsersV {
    + id,email,role,branch,service_states,active,auth_user_id
  }
  class "app.claims_version() = '2026-06-23.app_user_id+app_role'" as ClaimsVer
}

CurUid --> Users : id = app_user_id
IsAdmin --> CurUid
StateScope --> CurUid
CanReadDoc --> IsAdmin
CanReadDoc --> StateScope
CanReadDoc --> CurUid

' ---- engine server path (service-role, RLS bypassed) ----
package "Engine server path (trusted, service_role)" {
  class ctxFromRequest {
    + verify bearer (Supabase JWKS / Google transition)
    + read app_user_id (u178) + app_role
  }
  class "resolveActorToCtx(app_user_id)" as Resolve {
    + reads app.users_v BY id (NOT tabUser by email)
    + Ctx{ user=email, appUserId=u178, roles, unrestricted=is_admin }
  }
  class "queryConditions / service.js" as QC {
    + owner stamped = ctx.appUserId (u178)  <-- C9.3 FIX
    + owner filter = ctx.appUserId
    + unrestricted(is_admin) -> no filter
    + PRIMARY enforcer (engine callers)
  }
  class SupabaseStore_PgStore {
    + SERVICE_ROLE / direct-PG ; RLS BYPASSED
  }
}

GoTrue --> ctxFromRequest : session JWT (bearer)
ctxFromRequest --> Resolve
Resolve --> UsersV : read actor by id
Resolve --> QC
QC --> SupabaseStore_PgStore : scoped reads (owner = u178)

' ---- non-engine path (anon/auth key, RLS enforced via the live helper) ----
package "Non-engine path (browser / installer / portal)" {
  class AnonAuthClient {
    + SUPABASE_ANON_KEY + GoTrue JWT
    + request.jwt.claims POPULATED ; app.current_uid() = u178
    + installer/customer carry NO app_user_id -> DENIED (C1 scope)
  }
  class "tabCustomer_read policy (generated)" as CustPolicy {
    + service_role: using(true)
    + authenticated: USING (true)  <- TEAM-VISIBLE (no state col, plain docperm)
    + (state-scoped doctype would call app.can_read_doc(owner, <state-col>))
    + (if_owner doctype -> app.can_read_doc(owner, NULL))
  }
  class tabDocType {
    + ... existing meta cols ...
    + rls_policy_name : text   <<NEW, C4>>
    + permission_intent : text <<NEW, C4>>
  }
}

GoTrue --> AnonAuthClient : session JWT
AnonAuthClient --> CustPolicy : carries app_user_id claim
CustPolicy ..> CanReadDoc : state/if_owner doctypes call the LIVE predicate
CustPolicy ..> tabDocType : named by rls_policy_name / intent
QC ..> ClaimsVer : engine asserts claim contract

note as OwnerNote
  C9 RESOLVED against the SHIPPED hook:
  * owner keyspace = app_user_id (u178), back-filled from email
  * NO branch/role claim read in any policy
  * admin = app.is_admin() ; state read live (K7)
  * User doctype is READ-ONLY: reads via app.users_v; create/write/delete docperm-denied
    (assertCan/assertCanMutate 403 before store) -- provisioning via CRM provisionSupabaseUser (Rev-3.1/C13)
  * Customer = team-visible USING(true) (matches its plain-grant docperm)
end note
CustPolicy .. OwnerNote
QC .. OwnerNote

note as DisjointNote
  C3 - DISJOINT guard sets (not a cross-check):
  * Engine callers run queryConditions, bypass RLS -> a queryConditions bug has NO DB net.
  * Non-engine callers never run queryConditions -> RLS (can_read_doc) is their ONLY protection.
end note
QC .. DisjointNote
CustPolicy .. DisjointNote

' ---- test client (C2): sole RLS coverage, OUTSIDE the Store hierarchy ----
class "scripts/rls-probe.mjs" as RlsProbe {
  + raw supabase-js, ANON key
  + mints real session via supabase-session.js (real app_user_id claim)
  + SOLE RLS coverage; not in Store hierarchy
  + positive (actor sees rows) + negative (anon sees zero)
  + MUST run under anon/auth JWT (service-role would mask a broken policy)
}
RlsProbe --> CustPolicy : tests positive + negative

' ===========================================================================
' PART B: slice-1 constraint emission (C6, C7) + C10/C11 guards - ONE meta source
' ===========================================================================

package "Meta = single source of truth (adr-meta-as-data)" {
  class tabDocField {
    + fieldname, fieldtype
    + reqd, unique : boolean
    + options : text (Link/Table target)
    + fetch_from : text
  }
}

package "Two outputs from the SAME meta (DRY: emitted, not re-authored)" {
  class "JS validators (friendly message)" as JsValidators {
    + validateAgainstMeta: reqd/Select/numeric/Check/unique
    + validateLinks: Link existence (TOCTOU read-then-write)
  }
  class "ddl.js emitter (fail-fast DB net)" as DdlEmitter {
    + UNIQUE index  <- field.unique  (C6; C11 dedup precheck on populated)
    + FK <- Link.options (C6; C10 target-table-exists, LATER alter pass)
    + create trigger <- set_doc_stamps()  (C7)
    + NOT NULL / CHECK : DEFERRED (B.4)
  }
  class set_doc_stamps {
    + BEFORE INSERT/UPDATE
    + creation = coalesce(creation, now())
    + modified = now()  (AUTHORITATIVE ; C12 benign)
  }
}

tabDocField --> JsValidators : read by
tabDocField --> DdlEmitter : read by (SAME rows)
DdlEmitter --> set_doc_stamps : create trigger per table

note as DryNote
  DRY: one rule in META rows. JS gives the friendly field-level message;
  the DB constraint is the fail-fast / least-privilege net. Emitted from meta, never authored twice.
end note
JsValidators .. DryNote
DdlEmitter .. DryNote

note as O1Note
  O1: Zod = DEF structure (def-schema.js) + REQUEST envelopes (request-schemas.js) ONLY.
  Entity data validated by hand-rolled meta-driven JS (validateAgainstMeta / validateLinks) - NOT Zod.
  => Contract 4.1 "Zod is the only validation" must be amended.
end note
JsValidators .. O1Note

@enduml
